012%20years%2C%20Lev%20said%20the%20most%20common%20schema%20across%20all%20genders%20and%20cultures%20is%20unrelenting%20standards%2C%20a%20form%20of%20perfectionism.%20In%20relationships%2C%20it%20translates%20to%20%26quot%3Bfeelings%20of%20disappointment%2C%20being%20not%20good%20enough%2C%20trying%20harder%2C%20working%20harder%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20both%20in%20yourself%20and%20toward%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e05ba8f0-175c-4194-9804-5c3999c338ca%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECouples%20often%20have%20complementary%20%E2%80%94%20but%20opposing%20%E2%80%94%20beliefs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20being%20able%20to%20predict%20most%20couples'%20fights%2C%20Lev%20said%20that%20after%20looking%20at%20one%20person's%20schema%20results%2C%20she%20can%20almost%20always%20predict%20what%20their%20partner's%20schema%20will%20be.%20For%20instance%2C%20she's%20never%20seen%20a%20client%20with%20entitlement%20issues%20whose%20partner%20didn't%20have%20a%20tendency%20to%20self-sacrifice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEssentially%2C%20schemas%20function%20as%20more%20detailed%20versions%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-3-different-attachment-styles-2018-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eattachment%20styles%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20partners%20can%20attract%20or%20be%20attracted%20to%20people%20who%20trigger%20their%20attachment%20wounds.%26quot%3BOne%20person%20fears%20abandonment%2C%20the%20other%20person%20fears%20engulfment%2C%26quot%3B%20Lev%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20what%20can%20make%20fights%20so%20painful%20and%20impossible%20to%20wade%20through%3A%20they%20touch%20upon%20our%20most%20persistent%20beliefs%20about%20ourselves%20and%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20someone%20with%20unrelenting%20standards%20can%20criticize%20their%20partner%20for%20how%20they%20wash%20the%20dishes.%20If%20the%20other%20person%20has%20a%20fear%20of%20failure%2C%20they%20feel%20like%20they're%20walking%20on%