li%3EElon%20Musk%20is%20once%20again%20suing%20OpenAI%2C%20this%20time%20claiming%20he%20was%20%26quot%3Bdeceived%26quot%3B%20into%20cofounding%20the%20firm.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMusk's%20lawyers%20claim%20Altman%20and%20Brockman%20%26quot%3Bmanipulated%26quot%3B%20him%20by%20playing%20on%20his%20concerns%20about%20AI%20safety.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMusk%20first%20took%20legal%20action%20against%20OpenAI%20in%20March%20on%20similar%20grounds%20but%20dropped%20the%20suit%20in%20June.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EElon%20Musk%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20having%20another%20go%20at%20suing%20OpenAI%20and%20cofounders%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-chatgpt-openai-ceo-career-net-worth-ycombinator-prepper-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESam%20Altman%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Greg%20Brockman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20new%20lawsuit%20filed%20on%20Monday%2C%20Musk's%20lawyers%20argued%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhistory-of-openai-company-chatgpt-elon-musk-founded-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E%20executives%20%26quot%3Bdeceived%26quot%3B%20Musk%20into%20cofounding%20the%20company%20by%20playing%20on%20his%20concerns%20about%20the%20existential%20risks%20AI%20poses%20in%20what%20they%20describe%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Btextbook%20tale%20of%20altruism%20versus%20greed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk's%20lawyers%20also%20claimed%20that%20the%20billionaire%20was%20%26quot%3Bassiduously%20manipulated%26quot%3B%20by%20Altman%20and%20Brockman%20into%20cofounding%20OpenAI%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20that%20would%20focus%20on%20building%20AI%20safely%20with%20an%20open%20approach%20for%20the%20benefit%20of%20humanity.%20But%20the%20lawyers%20claimed%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Ball%20hot-air%20philanthropy%E2%80%94the%20hook%20for%20Altman's%20long%20con.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAfter%20Musk%20lent%20his%20name%20to%20the%20venture%2C%20invested%20significant%20time%2C%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20in%20seed%20capital%2C%20and%20recruited%20top%20AI%20scientists%20for%20OpenAI%2C%20Inc.%2C%20Musk%20and%20the%20non-profit's%20namesake%20objective%20were%20betrayed%20by%20Altman%20and%20his%20accomplices.%20The%20perfidy%20and%20deceit%20are%20of%20Shakespearean%20proportions%2C%26quot%3B%20Musk's%20lawyers%20argued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%20also%20stated%20that%20Musk%20was%20told%20OpenAI%20would%20hire%20leading%20scientists%20to%20compete%20with%20Google's%20DeepMind%20in%20a%20race%20to%20build%20artificial%20general%20intelligence%20(AGI).%20However%2C%20the%20lawyers%20argue%20that%20the%20company%20created%20a%20for-profit%20entity%20once%20it%20approached%20creating%20AGI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAltman%2C%20Musk%2C%20and%20Brockman%20founded%20OpenAI%20in%20December%202015%20as%20a%20nonprofit%20research%20lab.%20Musk%20departed%20in%202018%2C%20but%20his%20lawyers%20said%20in%20the%20first%20lawsuit%20that%20he%20%26quot%3Bcontinued%20to%20make%20contributions%20to%20OpenAI%26quot%3B%20until%20mid-September%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20now%20describes%20itself%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bcapped-profit%26quot%3B%20company.%20In%202019%2C%20it%20created%20OpenAI%20LP%2C%20a%20for-profit%20and%20nonprofit%20hybrid.%20In%20a%20blog%20post%20at%20the%20time%2C%20OpenAI%20said%20the%20idea%20was%20for%20investors%20and%20employees%20to%20get%20a%20%26quot%3Bcapped%20return%26quot%3B%20if%20it%20successfully%20achieved%20its%20mission.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk's%20lawyers%20describe%20the%20transition%20to%20a%20hybrid%20structure%20as%20a%20shift%20to%20%26quot%3Ba%20vehicle%20for%20Altman%20and%20his%20partners'%20self-enrichment%26quot%3B%20which%20they%20argue%20is%20evident%20in%20its%20partnership%20with%20Microsoft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20set%20up%20his%20own%20AI%20firm%2C%20xAI%2C%20in%202023.%20The%20mission%20of%20the%20for-