oung%20Bangladeshis%20are%20out%20of%20work%2C%20according%20to%20government%20figures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E-%20Economic%20rise%20-%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHasina%20was%2027%20and%20travelling%20abroad%20when%20renegade%20military%20officers%20murdered%20her%20father%2C%20prime%20minister%20Sheikh%20Mujibur%20Rahman%2C%20along%20with%20her%20mother%20and%20three%20brothers%20in%20a%201975%20coup.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20returned%20after%20living%20in%20exile%20for%20six%20years%20to%20take%20the%20reins%20of%20her%20father's%20Awami%20League%20party%2C%20beginning%20a%20decade-long%20struggle%20that%20saw%20her%20subjected%20to%20lengthy%20stretches%20of%20house%20arrest.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHasina%20joined%20forces%20with%20Khaleda%20Zia's%20Bangladesh%20Nationalist%20Party%20(BNP)%20to%20help%20oust%20military%20dictator%20Hussain%20Muhammad%20Ershad%20in%201990.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20they%20soon%20fell%20out%20and%20their%20ensuing%20rivalry%20has%20since%20dominated%20Bangladeshi%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHasina%20first%20served%20a%20term%20as%20prime%20minister%20in%201996%2C%20but%20lost%20to%20Zia%20five%20years%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20pair%20were%20then%20imprisoned%20on%20corruption%20charges%20in%202007%20after%20a%20coup%20by%20a%20military-backed%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20charges%20were%20dropped%20and%20they%20were%20free%20to%20contest%20an%20election%20the%20following%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHasina%20won%20in%20a%20landslide%20and%20has%20been%20in%20power%20ever%20since.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2078-year-old%20Zia%20meanwhile%20is%20in%20ailing%20health%20and%20confined%20to%20hospital%20after%20graft%20charges%20saw%20her%20sentenced%20to%20a%2017-year%20prison%20term%20in%202018%2C%20with%20top%20leaders%20from%20her%20party%20also%20behind%20bars.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHasina%20has%20been%20praised%20by%20supporters%20for%20leading%20Bangladesh%20through%20a%20remarkable%20economic%20boom%2C%20largely%20on%20the%20back%20of%20the%20mostly%20female%20factory%20workforce%20powering%20its%20garment%20export%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBangladesh%2C%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20poorest%20countries%20when%20it%20gained%20independence%20from%20Pakistan%20in%201971%2C%20has%20grown%20an%20average%20of%20more%20than%20six%20percent%20each%20year%20since%202009.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPoverty%20has%20plummeted%20and%20more%20than%2095%20percent%20of%20the%20country's%20170%20million%20people%20now%20have%20access%20to%20electricity%2C%20with%20per%20capita%20income%20overtaking%20India%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHasina%20also%20received%20international%20acclaim%20for%20opening%20Bangladesh's%20doors%20to%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20Rohingya%20refugees%20fleeing%20a%202017%20military%20crackdown%20in%20neighbouring%20Myanmar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20she%20has%20been%20hailed%20for%20a%20decisive%20crackdown%20on%20Islamist%20militants%20in%20the%20Muslim-majority%20nation%20after%20five%20homegrown%20extremists%20stormed%20a%20Dhaka%20cafe%20popular%20with%20Western%20expatriates%20and%20killed%2022%20people%20in%202016.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E-%20Silencing%20dissent%20-%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20her%20government's%20intolerance%20towards%20dissent%20has%20given%20rise%20to%20resentment%20at%20home%20and%20expressions%20of%20concern%20from%20Washington%20and%20elsewhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFive%20top%20Islamist%20leaders%20and%20a%20senior%20opposition%20figure%20were%20executed%20over%20the%20past%20decade%20after%20convictions%20for%20crimes%20against%20humanity%20committed%20during%20the%20country's%20brutal%201971%20liberation%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20healing%20the%20wounds%20of%20that%20conflict%2C%20the%20trials%20triggered%20mass%20protests%20and%20deadly%20clashes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20opponents%20branded%20them%20a%20farce%2C%20saying%20they%20were%20a%20politically%