0Missed%20Opportunities%3A%20How%20India%20Lost%20%2411%20Trillion%20Between%201971%20And%201991%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-08%2Fnj730ero_economy_625x300_05_August_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20India's%20Independence%20Day%20just%20days%20away%2C%20let's%20take%20a%20look%20at%20the%20country's%20economy.%20This%20year%2C%20the%20world%20economy%20is%20expected%20to%20grow%20at%203.%25.%20But%20India%20is%20expected%20to%20grow%20at%207%25%2C%20which%20is%20over%20twice%20as%20fast.%20We%20can%20be%20happy%20that%20India%20has%20become%20the%20fifth-largest%20economy%20in%20the%20world%20and%20look%20forward%20to%20becoming%20the%20third-largest%20soon.%20But%20in%20per%20capita%20terms%2C%20India%20could%20have%20done%20a%20lot%20better%2C%20if%20not%20for%20mistakes%20of%20the%20past.%20Our%20per%20capita%20GDP%20is%20%242%2C731%2C%20which%20is%20only%2020%25%20of%20the%20world%20GDP%20per%20capita%20of%20%2413%2C840.%20This%20percentage%20has%20been%20going%20up%20for%20many%20years%20now.%20In%202014%2C%20it%20was%20at%2014%25.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%20next%20fact%20might%20come%20as%20a%20surprise.%20Around%20the%20time%20of%20independence%2C%20this%20percentage%20was%20already%20at%2018%25.%20Why%20did%20it%20take%20over%2070%20years%20to%20go%20from%2018%25%20to%2020%25%3F%20Because%20things%20went%20horribly%20wrong%20in%20between.%20The%20Nehruvian%20economic%20model%20adopted%20after%20independence%20cost%20India.%20By%201991%2C%20India's%20per%20capita%20GDP%20had%20shrunk%20to%20just%206%25%20of%20the%20world's%20per%20capita%20GDP.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20India%20became%20three%20times%20poorer%20in%20four%20decades%20of%20Nehruvian%20socialism.%20During%20these%20years%2C%20India's%20economy%20performed%20worse%20than%20almost%20every%20other%20country's%3A%20worse%20than%20the%20countries%20of%20the%20West%2C%20worse%20than%20sub-Saharan%20Africa%2C%20and%20yes%2C%20even%20worse%20than%20Pakistan.%20By%201991%2C%20the%20average%20person%20in%20Pakistan%20was%20about%2026%25%20richer%20than%20the%20average%20Indian.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20Much%20Money%20Did%20India%20Lose%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20how%20much%20money%20did%20India%20lose%20by%20falling%20behind%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%3F%20To%20our%20surprise%2C%20nobody%20seems%20to%20have%20added%20it%20up%20before.%20But%20we%20can%20easily%20look%20up%20the%20numbers%20in%20the%20World%20Bank%20database.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5CnIn%201961%2C%20India's%20per%20capita%20GDP%20was%20%2483%2C%20while%20the%20world%20per%20capita%20GDP%20was%20%24450.%20By%201991%2C%20the%20latter%20increased%20to%20%244%2C426.%20What%20if%20India%20had%20grown%20at%20the%20same%20rate%3F%20Then%20our%20per%20capita%20GDP%20should%20have%20been%20%24816.%20Instead%2C%20we%20only%20managed%20to%20reach%20%24304%20in%201991.%20That%20works%20out%20to%20a%20loss%20of%20%24512%20per%20Indian.%20Multiply%20this%20by%20the%20population%2C%20and%20it%20comes%20up%20to%20%24455%20billion.%20Multiply%20that%20by%20inflation%2C%20and%20the%20loss%20is%20%241%2C051%20billion.%20An%20astonishing%20amount%20of%20over%20one%20trillion%20dollars%20in%201991%20alone.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5CnBut%20wait!%20That%20is%20just%20the%20loss%20for%20one%20year.%20We%20still%20have%20to%20look%20at%20the%20other%20years.%20We%20started%20with%20the%20year%201971%2C%20allowing%20a%20%26quot%3Bgrace%20period%26quot%3B%20of%2020%20years%20since%20India%20became%20a%20republic.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5CnThese%20aren't%20just%20dry%20numbers%20either.%20There%20is%20a%20fascinating%20pattern%20that%20matches%20the%20politics.%20For%201971%2C%20the%20loss%20was%20%24196%20billion.%20For%20the%20year%201975%2C%20the%20loss%20was%20over%20twice%20as%20much%2C%20at%20%24414%20billion.%20So%2C%20the%20downfall%20between%201971%20and%201975%20was%20rapid.%20Note%20that%20these%20are%20also%20the%20years%20leading%20up%20to%20the%20Emergency.%20By%201975%2C%20India%20was%20drowning%20due%20to%2025%20years%20of%20failed%20economic%20policy.%20Inflation%20ran%20at%2029%25%20the%20year%20before%2C%20and%20GDP%20growth%20was%20down%20to%201%25.%20The%20Indira%20Gandhi%20government%20first%20seized%20private%20banks%2C%20then%20foreign%20investments%2C%20then%20middle-class%20savings%2C%20then%20everyday%20food%2C%20and%20finally%2C%20democracy%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELosses%20After%201975%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%201975%2C%20we%20see%20a%20relatively%20stable%20phase%20in%20the%20data.%20India%20was%20still%20losing%20huge%20amounts%20of%20money%20because%20of%20tepid%20growth%20rates%2C%20but%20the%20losses%20remained%20between%20%24400%20billion%20and%20%24600%20billion%20a%20year.%20This%20phase%20lasted%20till%201985.%20The%20final%20collapse%20started%20in%201986%2C%20as%20Rajiv%20Gandhi's%20policies%20began%20to%20take%20effect.%20The%20losses%20mounted%20quickly%3A%20%24450%20billion%20in%201985%2C%20%24600%20billion%20in%201986%2C%20and%20nearly%20%24800%20billion%20in%201988%20and%201989.%20Almost%20%24900%20billion%20in%201990%2C%20and%20finally%2C%20over%20one%20trillion%20dollars%20in%201991.%20In%20total%2C%20the%20loss%20to%20the%20Indian%20economy%20between%201971%20and%201991%20works%20out%20to%20a%20mind-boggling%20%2411.246%20trillion.%20That%20amounts%20to%20Rs%20942%20lakh%20crore.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5CnIt%20is%20difficult%20to%20put%20such%20astronomical%20numbers%20into%20context.%20For%20the%20current%20financial%20year%2C%20the%20budget%20of%20the%20Union%20Government%20is%20around%20Rs%2048%20lakh%20crore.%20We%20wonder%20how%20many%20factories%2C%20schools%2C%20hospitals%2C%20roads%2C%20airports%2C%20railways%2C%20tanks%2C%20ships%20and%20planes%20we%20could%20have%20had%20for%20Rs%20942%20lakh%20crore.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5CnThis%20Independence%20Day%2C%20we%20might%20as%20well%20draw%20a%20lesson%20from%20the%20past.%20After%20all%2C%20we%20have%20collectively%20paid%20Rs%20942%20lakh%20crore%20for%20it.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cem%3E(Abhishek%20Banerjee%20is%20an%20author%20and%20columnist%20and%20Karuna%20Gopal%20is%20President%2C%20Foundation%20for%20Futuristic%20Cities.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722851820000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-08%2F7snpj668_economy_625x300_05_August_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fcase-of-missed-opportunity-how-india-lost-11-trillion-between-1971-and-1991-6267425%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20total%2C%20the%20loss%20to%20the%20Indian%20economy%20between%201971%20and%201991%20works%20out%20to%20a%20mind-boggling%20%2411.246%20trillion.%20That%20amounts%20to%20Rs%20942%20lakh%20crore.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fcase-of-missed-opportunity-how-india-lost-11-trillion-between-1971-and-1991-6267425%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fcase-of-missed-opportunity-how-india-lost-11-trillion-between-1971-and-1991-6267425%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fcase-of-missed-opportunity-how-india-lost-11-trillion-between-1971-and-1991-6267425%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Raha%20enjoys%20a%20car%20ride%20with%20mumma%20Alia%20Bhatt%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722851720000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-112286877%2Cimgsize-70626.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https