h%20as%20Rs%205%20lakh%20for%20a%20tiger%20jaw%2C%20while%20a%20leopard%20jaw%20goes%20for%20Rs%202%20lakh%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20sighs.%20Pointing%20to%20how%20futile%20it%20is%20to%20engage%20in%20such%20trading%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20not%20even%20as%20if%20one%20is%20making%20medicines%20out%20of%20these%20parts.%20It%20is%20purely%20for%20cultural%20and%20aesthetic%20reasons.%20So%20why%20should%20animals%20be%20killed%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThrough%20Arunachal%20Ivory%20and%20Ornaments%2C%20Nabam%2C%20Likha%20and%20their%20friend%20Anang%20Tadar%20are%20marking%20a%20first%20by%203D%20printing%20the%20animal%20parts%20to%20offer%20the%20tribes%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F267925%2Fasif-khan-bambooka-bamboo-bicycle-features-cost-ecofriendly-buy%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esustainable%20alternatives%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElaborating%20on%20the%20process%2C%20Anang%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20animal%20parts%20that%20we%20are%20dealing%20with%20are%20not%20plain%20surfaces%3B%20they%20have%20complex%20structures.%20So%2C%20while%203D%20printing%2C%20we%20have%20to%20ensure%20that%20all%20the%20details%20are%20accurately%20scanned.%20It%20took%20us%20almost%20two%20years%20to%20finalise%20the%20process%2C%20and%20it%20is%20still%20ongoing.%20When%20working%20with%20such%20materials%2C%20there%20are%20always%20chances%20that%20the%20next%20print%20might%20be%20better%20than%20the%20first%2C%20so%20we%20have%20to%20keep%20making%20versions.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ftribes-4-1722420132.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20blend%20of%20eco%20friendly%20resins%20are%20used%20while%20producing%20the%20replicas%20of%20the%20an